01/07/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu urged all politicians Thursday (30 June) to make sincere efforts in completing necessary judicial reforms. He also called on prosecutors, judges and policemen to contribute to the process. Basescu added that this would be a long road and stressed that employees of all relevant institutions must change their mindset for reforms to be successful. He reiterated that the establishment of an efficient, transparent and independent judicial system is a top priority for Romanian authorities, while stressing that what EU wants to see is "real progress, not perfection". (Rompres - 30/06/05)
